image → (B, G, R)
In a traditional way, we store the image in RGB order.

Let's try to convert BRG to RGB

In [ ]:
def plt_imshow(image, title="No name"):
  image = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
  plt.imshow(image)
  plt.xticks([])
  plt.yticks([])
  plt.title(title)
  plt.show

Image Transformation¶

  • warpAffine

Image shifting

In [ ]:
M = np.float32([[1, 0, 25], [0, 1, 50]]) # For shifting 25 in x-axis, 50 in y-axis
shifted = cv2.warpAffine(image, M, (image.shape[1], image.shape[0]))
plt_imshow(shifted, "Shifted by 25 in x, by 50 in y")
In [ ]:
shifted = imutils.translate(image, 25, 50)
plt_imshow(shifted, "Shifted by imutils.translate")

Image rotation

  • getRotationMatrix2D
In [ ]:
(h, w) = image.shape[:2]
(cX, cY) = (w//2, h//2)
M = cv2.getRotationMatrix2D((cX,cY), -45, 1)
rotated = cv2.warpAffine(image, M, (image.shape[1], image.shape[0]))
plt_imshow(rotated, "Rotated by 45 degrees")
In [ ]:
rotated = imutils.rotate_bound(image, 45)
plt_imshow(rotated, "Rotated by imutils.rotate_bound")
In [ ]:
rotated = imutils.rotate(image, 45)
plt_imshow(rotated)
In [ ]:
resized = cv2.resize(image, (100,100))
plt_imshow(resized, "Resized to 100 x 100")
In [ ]:
image.shape
Out[ ]:
(168, 300, 3)

168 x 300 → 100 x 100

Height changed from 168 to 100 (100/168 → 59.52% resizing)

Width changed from 300 to 100 (100/300 → 33.33% resizing)

We would like to keep same aspect ratio even after resizing

Let's resize the image to have a height 500 pixels with the same aspect ratio

In [ ]:
r = 100/image.shape[0] # r = 0.5952
dim = (int(image.shape[1]*r), 100) # destination image size (width, height)

resized = cv2.resize(image, dim)
plt_imshow(resized, "Resized with the same aspect ratio")

Image flipping¶

flip(src, flip code)
  • flip code == 1 → horizontal flip
  • flip code == 0 → vertical flip
  • flip code == -1 → both
In [ ]:
flipped = cv2.flip(image, -1)
plt_imshow(flipped, "Flipped vertically and horizontally")
